# Project: embedded agentic QA capability

We build AI agents that drop into a PARTNER's existing CI/CD, source control, and trust boundary
and drive their web app under test via Playwright MCP. This is NOT a standalone product:
no multi-tenant control plane, no billing, no dashboards, no onboarding UI.

Four agents (build first two only for now; stub the rest):
- Regression Triager — classifies run failures into {product bug, flaky, env/infra, test-needs-update}.
- Self-Healer — repairs broken test LOCATORS and navigation; ships a PR.
- Scenario Author (STUB) — requirements -> executable scenarios.
- Coverage Analyst (STUB) — finds coverage gaps.

Substrate: the App Model — a versioned semantic locator graph that every agent reads/writes.
Build the App Model and the evidence/trace pipeline BEFORE the agents; nothing is reliable without them.

Stack: TypeScript (Node 20+), pnpm workspaces monorepo, zod for all I/O schemas,
Drizzle + Postgres + pgvector, S3-compatible object storage (MinIO locally, content-addressed),
Playwright MCP via the MCP TypeScript SDK, vitest for tests + eval harness.
Orchestration: a typed in-process Runner with idempotency now; a Temporal adapter is a future seam.
Provider-agnostic model gateway; pin model snapshots; temperature 0 where the task allows.
